quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  65,1,"O Prophet! ňĻInstruct the believers:ňļ When you ňĻintend toňļ divorce women, then divorce them with concern for their waiting period,¬†and count it accurately. And¬†fear God, your Lord. Do not force them out of their homes, nor should they leave‚ÄĒunless they commit a blatant misconduct. These are the limits set by God. And whoever transgresses God‚Äôs limits has truly wronged his own soul. You never know, perhaps God will bring about a change ňĻof heartňļ later"
  65,2,"Then when they have ňĻalmostňļ reached the end of their waiting period, either retain them honourably or separate from them honourably.¬†And call two of your reliable men to witness ňĻeither wayňļ‚ÄĒand ňĻlet the witnessesňļ bear true testimony for ňĻthe sake ofňļ God. This is enjoined on whoever has faith in God and the Last Day. And whoever is mindful of God, He will make a way out for them"
  65,3,"and provide for them from sources they could never imagine. And whoever puts their trust in God, then He ňĻaloneňļ is sufficient for them. Certainly God achieves His Will. God has already set a destiny for everything"
  65,4,"As for your women past the age of menstruation, in case you do not know, their waiting period is three months, and those who have not menstruated as well. As for those who are pregnant, their waiting period ends with delivery.¬†And whoever is mindful of God, He will make their matters easy for them"
  65,5,"This is the commandment of God, which He has revealed to you. And whoever is mindful of God, He will absolve them of their sins and reward them immensely"
  65,6,"Let them live where you live ňĻduring their waiting periodňļ, according to your means. And do not harass them to make their stay unbearable. If they are pregnant, then maintain them until they deliver. And if they nurse your child,¬†compensate them, and consult together courteously. But if you fail to reach an agreement, then another woman will nurse ňĻthe childňļ for the father"
  65,7,"Let the man of wealth provide according to his means. As for the one with limited resources, let him provide according to whatever God has given him. God does not require of any soul beyond what He has given it. After hardship, God will bring about ease"
  65,8,"ňĻImagineňļ how many societies rebelled against the commandments of their Lord and His messengers, so We called each ňĻsocietyňļ to a severe account and subjected them to a horrible punishment"
  65,9,"So they tasted the evil consequences of their doings, and the outcome of their doings was ňĻtotalňļ loss"
  65,10,"God has ňĻalsoňļ prepared for them a severe punishment. So fear God, O people of reason and faith. God has indeed revealed to you a Reminder"
  65,11,"ňĻand sentňļ a messenger reciting to you God‚Äôs revelations, making things clear so that He may bring those who believe and do good out of darkness and into light. And whoever believes in God and does good will be admitted by Him into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there for ever and ever. God will have indeed granted them an excellent provision"
  65,12,"God is the One Who created seven heavens ňĻin layersňļ, and likewise for the earth. The ňĻdivineňļ command descends between them so you may know that God is Most Capable of everything and that God certainly encompasses all things in ňĻHisňļ knowledge"